    "challenging.",
    "This ambiguity hinders end-users and stakeholders from understanding the specific purposes and uses of AI in healthcare settings.",
    "While QPs involving human subjects are typically overseen by Institutional Review Boards (IRBs) as required by the Common Rule (45 CFR 46) 7, clinical QPs usually adhere to accreditation standards set by organizations like the Joint Commission.",
    "However, the integration of AI and large language models (LLMs) into hospital EHR systems currently lacks a defined oversight framework (Table 1) 2.",
    "Additionally, there is no established ethical or legal requirement in the United States for obtaining informed consent for the use of medical AI in clinical practice."
